==English==
===Adjective===

'''Steadfast'''

#Fixed or unchanging; [[steady]].
#Firmly loyal or constant; unswerving.

'''Etymology'''
''Steadfast'' comes from [[Middle English]] ''stedefast'' which in turn comes from [[Old English]] ''stedefæst''. It is comprised of to parts ''stede'' which means place and ''fæst'', fixed.

